								<p>1976- Dart Gallery, Chicago, IL</p>
								<p>1974- Painting and Sculpture Today, Indianapolis Museum of Art, Indianapolis, IN</p>
								<p>1974- Allan Stone Gallery, New York, NY</p>
								<p>1970- Society for Contemporary Art, The Art Institute of Chicago, Chicago, IL</p>
								<p>1968- Whitney Museum of American Art, New York, NY</p>
								<p>1968- State Museum of Natural History and Art, Springfield, IL</p>
								<p>1968- Five Abstractionists, Main Street Gallery, Chicago, IL</p>
								<p>1968- Painting: Off the Wall, Des Moines Art Center, IA</p>
								<p>1966- Noah Goldowsky Gallery, New York, NY</p>
								<p>1965- Society for Contemporary Art, The Art Institute of Chicago, Chicago, IL</p>
								<p>1964- Contemporary Latvian Painters, Herron Museum of Art, Indianapolis, IN</p>
								<p>1964- 7’and Up, DePaul University, Chicago, IL</p>
								<p>1964- Hyde Park Art Center, Chicago, IL</p>
								<p>1962- 12 Chicago Artists, McCormick Place Gallery, Chicago, IL</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="tab w-full overflow-hidden border-t">
							<input class="absolute opacity-0" id="tab-single-three" type="radio" name="tabs2">
							<label class="block py-3 text-gray-600 text-lg font-medium leading-normal cursor-pointer" for="tab-single-three">Permanent Collections</label>
							<div class="tab-content overflow-hidden leading-normal pl-4">
								<p>Chase Manhattan Bank, New York, NY</p>
								<p>AT&T Company, New York, NY</p>
								<p>HMH Publishing Company, Chicago, IL</p>
								<p>Houstonic Museum of Art, Bridgeport, CT</p>
								<p>Herbert F. Johnson Museum of Art, Ithaca, NY</p>
								<p>Kunsthaus, Zurich, Switzerland</p>
								<p>Latvian State Museum of Art, Riga, Latvia</p>
								<p>The Sydney and Francis Lewis Foundation, VA</p>
								<p>Minneapolis Institute of Arts, Minneapolis, MN</p>
								<p>Newark Museum, Newark, NJ</p>
								<p>Museum of Contemporary Art, Chicago, IL</p>
								<p>Phoenix Museum of Art, Phoenix, AZ</p>
								<p>Ringling Museum of Art, Sarasota, FL</p>
								<p>St. Mary’s College of Art, MD</p>
								<p>University Art Center, Rutgers State University, NJ</p>
							</div>
						</div>

					</section>

					<section class="md:my-12 content">
						<h2 class="text-gray-800 text-2xl mt-10 mb-2">Bibliography</h2>
						<div class="tab w-full overflow-hidden border-t">
							<input class="absolute opacity-0" id="tab-single-four" type="radio" name="tabs2">
							<label class="block py-3 text-gray-600 text-lg font-medium leading-normal cursor-pointer" for="tab-single-four">Citations</label>
							<div class="tab-content overflow-hidden  leading-normal pl-4">
								<p class="">Edvins Strautmanis, Abstract Painter, 58.
								<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/1992/08/08/obituaries/edvins-strautmanis-abstract-painter-58.html" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">The New York Times</a>.</p>
									
									<p class="">Stony Brook University Catalog.
								<a href="https://ir.stonybrook.edu/xmlui/bitstream/handle/11401/2930/Art_Piece_53.pdf?sequence=1" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">SUNY Stony Brook [PDF]</a>.</p>
									
									<p class="">Nathan Manilow Sculpture Park Collection.<a href="http://www.publicartinchicago.com/nathan-manilow-sculpture-park-nmsp-collection-phoenix-by-edvins-strautmanis/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Public Art in Chicago</a>.</p>
									
									<p class="">Cēsis Art Festival 2019.
								<a href="https://arterritory.com/en/visual_arts/articles/24195-cesis_art_festival_2019_highlights/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Art Territory</a>.</p>
									
									<p class="">Roberta Pancoast Smith on Edvins Strautmanis. <a href="https://www.artforum.com/print/reviews/197304/edvins-strautmanis-71501" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Art Forum</a>.</p>

							</div>
						</div>

					</section>
				</div>

				<section class="my-12">
					<h2 class="text-gray-800 text-2xl mt-4 mb-2">Video &amp; Other Media</h2>

					<div class="flex flex-wrap -mx-2">
						<div class="w-full md:w-1/2 px-2">
							<h3 class="mb-2 text-gray-700 text-lg font-medium">Portrait of a Painter</h3>
							<div class=" relative aspect-ratio-16/9 ">

								<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/yL0sD5oXarA" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay;modestbranding=1; controls=0;encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; rel=0" allowfullscreen class="absolute left-0 top-0 w-full h-full object-cover"></iframe>

							</div>
							<p class="text-gray-700 p-2 leading-relaxed mt-2">
								A narrated film by
								<strong>Michel Auder</strong>
								showing Strautmanis at work in his SOHO studio. Made in 1983 when Strautmanis was at the peak of his career the  brief narrated film includes a tour of the artist's SOHO loft.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="w-full md:w-1/2 px-2">
							<h3 class="mb-2 text-gray-700 text-lg font-medium">Images/Art New York</h3>
							<div class="relative aspect-ratio-16/9">
								<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/L9Q23Ah6VrE" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; modestbranding=1; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen class="absolute left-0 top-0 w-full h-full object-cover"></iframe>
							</div>
							<p class="text-gray-700 p-2 leading-relaxed  mt-2">
								An extended interview, a tour of the artist's SOHO studio and unique footage of Strautmanis at work. Produced and Directed by
								<strong>Bill Page</strong>
								for
								<strong>New York One</strong>.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="w-full md:w-1/2 px-2">
							<h3 class="mb-2 text-gray-700 text-lg font-medium">SUNY Stony Brook - 1996</h3>
							<div class="relative aspect-ratio-16/9">
								<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/CO0lfNrzeyY" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen class="absolute left-0 top-0 w-full h-full object-cover"></iframe>
							</div>
							<p class="text-gray-700 p-2 leading-relaxed  mt-2">
								An overview of Strautmanis' 1996 exhibition at the State University of New York, Stony Brook.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>
		
			</main>
			<script>
				/* Optional Javascript to close the radio button version by clicking it again */
var myRadios = document.getElementsByName('tabs2');
var setCheck;
var x = 0;
for (x = 0; x < myRadios.length; x = x + 1)
{

myRadios[x].onclick = function ()
{

if (setCheck != this)
{

setCheck = this;

}
else
{

this.checked = false;
setCheck = null;

}

};

}
			</script>

